# How It Works

## How the system works

The system captures the rhythm, speed, and flow of your gesture and translates it into emotional features.
These features guide the generation of a poetic reflection and a set of music suggestions.

This explains how the system works and how your interaction is interpreted.

---

## What to draw

You do not need to draw anything specific.
Simply create free lines or gestures.

The system interprets movement, not shapes.

This means you are not required to draw objects, symbols, or recognizable forms.

---

## Input and interaction

No tools are required.
You can use your finger or any available input device.

A touchscreen is required.
The experience is designed for direct touch interaction on mobile devices.

---

## Duration of the experience

The drawing phase lasts around 20 seconds, followed by a short processing time.
The full experience takes less than one minute.

---

## What you receive

After drawing, each interaction generates:

* a short poetic reflection
* a set of music suggestions aligned with your gesture

This is the result of your interaction.

---

## Beta access and waiting list

The beta is currently limited.

Requesting access will add you to the waiting list.
Selected users will receive an email with instructions to access the app.

The full experience is available via app download, which will be shared with selected users.

---

## Language

The app interface is currently in English.

However, the assistant can understand and respond in multiple languages.

---

## Data and privacy

The system processes interaction data to generate responses.

No personal or biometric data is stored unless explicitly provided (e.g. email for beta access).

---

## Limitations

The assistant can only answer based on the available documents.

If information is not included, it may not provide a complete answer.

This explains why the assistant may sometimes not respond.

